						<div class="postbody">From Nestopia's NTSC filter attributes - Resolution, Sharpness, Color Bleed, Artifacts, and Fringing - which are affected by pixel clock conflict between NTSC standard and NES video signal, affected by imperfectly combined signals on the NES's part, and affected by a TV's imperfect Y/C separator?</div>

